{
  "texts": [
    "The architectures for the creation of medical imaging and molecular imaging biobanks must incorporate advanced high-performance computing capabilities to allow high-throughput processing.",
    "Nowadays, institutions gather a whole spectrum of mostly digital information, including social, clinical, imaging and pathological records together with genomic profiles.",
    "Consequently, modern biobanking is shifting its focus from sample-driven to data-driven strategies.",
    "This implies that data management and integration has become a major component of contemporary biomedical research.",
    "In particular, the transition to digital biobanks enabled the amalgamation of diverse datasets, necessitating sophisticated data management and integration techniques."
  ]
}